joehung302 wrote:
&gt; Let&#39;s say I want to partition the web into 3 disjoint partitions and I
&gt; define the 3 partitions as:
&gt;
&gt; 1. .com
&gt; 2. .edu
&gt; 3. dot everything else.
&gt;
&gt; I know I can setup SurtPrefix scope on the first 2 partitions. How do
&gt; I use SurtPrefix on the 3rd partition? Or should I use something else?

You might try using a decidingscope on the 3rd crawler adding two 
SurtPrefixedDecideRule rules -- One for &#39;.com&#39; and one for &#39;.edu&#39; -- 
only instead of ACCEPT if a match, instead you&#39;d REJECT (See the UI).  
There is also a NotSurtPrefixedDecideRule.

